Program: Outlook
Title: Apartheid and South African Township Music
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbr90
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
South African township music - a treasure trove of recordings re-released after 40 years, members of the Slo Foot King Brothers comment. Also, training moths to detect landmines. And, Belarus and memories of the Chernobyl nuclear disaster. Presenter: Frederick Dove.